' ----- DUP-10 PARTIAL: timer inventory (6 timers still undocumented) -----
package "DUP-10  Timer inventory" $TINT_PARTIAL {
  [DisplayEventManager._coalesce\n(DispatcherTimer, 250 ms)] as D10A
  [DisplayEventManager._burstTimer\n(System.Threading.Timer, 1 s x 10)] as D10B
  [EnvironmentalCurveService._curveTimer\n+ _curveEventThrottleTimer\n(both DispatcherTimer)] as D10C
  [DDCRecoveryService fallback worker\n(Task.Delay loop only while\nDDC candidates exist)] as D10D
  [NightLightRegistry._resendTimer\n(System.Threading.Timer, debounced resend)] as D10E
  [DisplayIdentifierService._timer\n(DispatcherTimer, overlay auto-hide)] as D10F
  [WPFLog._timer\n(System.Threading.Timer, async flush)] as D10G
  [ShellNotifyIcon._taskbarRecreateTimer\n(DispatcherTimer)] as D10H
  [NightLightSettingsHandler._deferredRegistryTimer\n(System.Threading.Timer; 6089fd8 NL flicker-fix)] as D10I
  [KnownDisplaysStore._stampDebounceTimer\n(System.Threading.Timer)] as D10J
  [BrightnessFlyout._activeRecoveryTooltipCloseTimer\n(DispatcherTimer)] as D10K
  [BrightnessFlyout._previewSweepTimer\n(DispatcherTimer, 50 ms cadence)] as D10L
  [AboutPage._staleTimer\n(DispatcherTimer)] as D10M
  [CurveEditor._currentTimeTimer\n(DispatcherTimer)] as D10N
  [EnvironmentalPage._curveSaveDebounceTimer\n(DispatcherTimer)] as D10O
  note bottom
    Each timer owns a distinct domain.
    TrayIconManager itself is event-driven (no internal timer).
    PARTIAL: six timers (D10I..D10O) still
    not documented in audits/notes; audit_21 F3
    proposed try/catch on threading-timer callbacks
    to prevent process tear-down (M-11 / D-11).
  end note
}

' ----- DUP-11 PARTIAL: hex color parsing (three slightly different copies) -----
package "DUP-11  Hex color parsing / formatting" $TINT_PARTIAL {
  [Visuals/AppTheme.cs\n.ParseHex / .ToHex\n(throws on bad input)] as D11A
  [Models/AppSettings.cs\nThemeColorOverride.TryParse / .ToHex\n(returns nullable, swallows on error)] as D11B
  [WPF/TAWPFColorPicker.xaml.cs\n.TryParseHex (ARGB or RGBA order,\n3/4/6/8-char input)] as D11C
  D11A -[#orange]- D11B : same 6/8-char branch,\ndifferent error policy
  D11A -[#orange]- D11C : color-picker accepts\nshort forms the others reject
  note bottom
    Three call-site shapes (validating ctor,
    nullable model getter, picker text input)
    are real - but the 6/8-char Convert.ToByte
    blocks are byte-for-byte parallel and
    could share a primitive.
  end note
}

' ----- DUP-12 PARTIAL: monitor-id prefix vocabulary -----
package "DUP-12  Monitor-id prefix vocabulary" $TINT_PARTIAL {
  [MonitorService.GetIdentityKey\n(produces edid: / port: / num:)] as D12A
  [DisplayEventManager.ExtractHwid\n(strips port: prefix,\nsplits DISPLAY\\... / MONITOR\\...)] as D12B
  [Models/Hotkey.cs HotkeyTarget\n(EdidPrefix const "edid:")] as D12C
  [Services/ProfileManager.cs\n(EdidIdPrefix const "edid:",\nlegacy migration only)] as D12D
  D12A -[#orange]- D12B : producer / consumer
  D12C -[#orange]- D12D : same literal,\ntwo private const fields
  note bottom
    The "edid:" / "port:" / "num:" tokens
    are produced in one place but each consumer
    re-declares its own const string for the
    prefix it cares about. Cheap to share via
    a small MonitorIdPrefixes static.
  end note
}

' ----- DUP-13 RESOLVED: hotkey paths route through Notify*Adjustment helper -----
package "DUP-13  Hotkey vs tray-scroll Notify discipline" $TINT_RESOLVED {
  [App.xaml.cs:AdjustAllMonitorBrightness\nApp.xaml.cs:AdjustNightLightBrightness\nApp.xaml.cs:ApplyOrRestoreBrightness] as D13A
  [App.xaml.cs:TrayScroll handler] as D13B
  [App.xaml.cs:Notify*Adjustment helper\n(single funnel)] as D13C
  D13A -[#green]- D13C : all hotkey paths now\ncall NotifyUserBrightnessAdjustment /\nNotifyUserNightLightAdjustment
  D13B -[#green]- D13C : tray scroll routes through\nthe same helper
  note bottom
    Wave-1 fix: hotkey and tray-scroll write paths
    share the same release-discipline funnel.
    Curve toggle stays lit while individuals
    auto-release consistently across both entry
    points (H-05 closed).
  end note
}

' ----- DUP-16 RESOLVED: Refresh inline promotion vs PromoteRecovered -----
package "DUP-16  Recovery promotion paths" $TINT_RESOLVED {
